    <note type="biography">
        <p>American minister and journalist. Studied theology at Yale. Minister to Congregational churches in Connecticut, 1834–49. Organiser of the Connecticut Free Soil party from about 1847. Editor of an anti-slavery newspater in Boston, Massachusetts, 1852–4. Acquired and restored to prosperity the <hi rend="italic">Worcester</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Mass.</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Daily Spy</hi> in 1859. Republican member of Congress for the Worcester district, 1862–9.</p></note>
